Senate Leader Ahmad Lawan (APC, Yobe) and the Minority Leader, Godswill Akpabio (PDP, Akwa Ibom), yesterday, traded words over the adjournment of sitting till next Tuesday. The two chambers of the National Assembly had adjourned sitting over the forthcoming local  government congress of the APC. Akpabio, a former governor of Akwa Ibom had while seconding the motion said the APC senators should be given the opportunity to prepare for a fight next Saturday.  He said the last Saturday’s ward congress of the APC was not a congress but a boxing bout. Lawan said only people who were free had time to fight, saying the PDP should continue to seek for the forgiveness of Nigerians over their misrule.